author: Staff
title: Hendrix reaches top 25 in volleyball
text:
Hendrix reaches top 25 in volleyball Posted: October 13, 2015 - 8:33pm HENDRIX SPORTS INFORMATION 
The Hendrix College volleyball team received the first nationally ranking in program history in this week’s AVCA Top 25 Poll. The Warriors, under fifth-year head coach Ryan Meek, are ranked 24th with a 15-6 record overall and a 9-0 mark in the Southern Athletic Association. 
“It’s great that the team is recognized for their hard work,” said Meek. “They have done a great job continuing to fight. Our long term goal is to win the SAA and make it to the NCAA Tournament again.” Hendrix ended the 2014 season receiving votes for the first time after a trip to the second round of the NCAA Tournament. 
This season, the Warriors have received votes in every poll and finally cracked the Top 25 on Tuesday. 
Hendrix has played a tough schedule this season with a win over No. 11 Carthage (then #4) and losses to No. 1 Washington (Mo.), No. 12 Wisconsin-Whitewater, No. 16 Elmhurst and No. 20 UT Dallas. 
The Warriors will host Rhodes College in SAA play at Grove Gymnasium in a Dig Pink match at 6 p.m. Wednesday.
